  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "BIM Modeller",
  "description": "<p>1. Prepare installation details, shop drawing layout and submission list</p>\n<p>2. Design, create and modify electrical circuits, cable containment routing, lighting fixtures</p>\n<p>3. Create and generate lighting switch, distribution board families and component library</p>\n<p>4. Create risers / electrical / LAN / M&amp;E Room etc, layout detail</p>\n<p>5. Attend site coordination meeting with customers / clients</p>\n<p>6. Perform clash report and solving the clasher with Project Engineer/Customer</p>\n<p>7. Verify and validate Design with zero clasher and adequate maintenance space</p>\n<p>8. Prepare visualization and walk through critical/Congested areas if necessary</p>\n<p>9. CSD and Roombook Coordination</p>\n<p>10. Generate bills of quantity for material required when necessary</p>\n<p>11. Any other required task from Main Contractor / Consultant / Client</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>1. Diploma or Degree in Electrical Engineering</p>\n<p>2. Knowledge of Autodesk REVIT and AutoCAD</p>\n<p>3. Able to read and visualise electrical systems and equipment drawings</p>\n<p>4. Able to create and modify electrical circuits based on the specification</p>\n<p>5. Able to create and modify cable containment routing based on specification and location</p>\n<p>6. Able to create 2D n 3D electrical views from BIM Model</p>\n<p>7. Able to set-up configurations for electrical model files</p>",
